{"cursor":"6863","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n\n'Tolkien's legendarium' is a fictional universe in J. R. R. Tolkien's [[The Lord\nof the Rings]], based on Tolkien's real-world knowledge of Anglo-Saxon beliefs.\nColloquially, it may refer to any or all of Tolkien's Middle-earth writing\nconsidered as a whole, thus including works such as [[The Hobbit]] and The Lord\nof the Rings. Specific to the literary discipline of Tolkien studies, it is the\npart of Tolkien's high fantasy fiction concerned with his Elven legends; that\nis, fictional historic events that have become legendary from the perspective of\nthe characters within [[The Lord of the Rings]].\n","linknr":275,"url":"Legendarium","recorded":1375077590,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Tolkien%27s_legendarium&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Tolkien%27s_legendarium&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Tolkien%27s_legendarium","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Legendarium&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Legendary_(disambiguation)","/wiki/Tolkien%27s_Legendarium","/wiki/Fictional_universe","/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien","/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings","/wiki/Middle-earth","/wiki/The_Hobbit","/wiki/Tolkien_studies","/wiki/High_fantasy","/wiki/Elf_(M